text: Theodor Rosetti Theodor Rosetti (5 May 1837, Iași or Solești, Moldavia - 17 July 1923, Bucharest, Romania) was a Romanian writer, journalist and politician who served as Prime Minister of Romania between 23 March 1888 and 22 March 1889.
